The paper discusses the use of Zero learning, a popular method in artificial intelligence, for board games. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a fully convolutional structure, which is a common technique in machine learning for image processing, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses training against checkpoints, which is a technique used in game theory and optimization, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
